‚≠ê 2. Problem LiveView solves

Traditional apps need frontend + backend

JavaScript handles UI changes

APIs sync data

More complexity and bugs

‚≠ê LiveView removes most of this complexity

‚≠ê 3. How LiveView works (simple flow)

User opens a web page

Browser connects to server using WebSocket

Server keeps page state

Data changes on server

Only updated parts are sent to browser

‚≠ê 4. What happens in the browser

Page does not reload

Only small HTML updates

Faster user experience

Smooth UI interactions

‚≠ê 5. Example without LiveView ‚ùå

Click button

Request sent

Page reloads

User waits

‚≠ê 6. Example with LiveView ‚úÖ

Click button

Server updates data

UI updates instantly

No page reload

‚≠ê 7. Real-world analogy üß†

